liblc3
------------------------------------------
The Low Complexity Communication Codec (LC3) is used by Bluetooth as the codec
for LE Audio. It enables high quality audio over the low bandwidth connections
provided by Bluetooth LE.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.5.3-1
  liblc3-devel-1.1.1-1bl1
  liblc3_1-1.1.1-1bl1
  pkg-config-2.2.0-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.42-1
  cygport-0.36.8-1
  gcc-core-11.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-11.4.0-1
  meson-1.2.3-1
  ninja-1.12.0-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/google/liblc3

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/google/liblc3/archive/refs/tags/v1.1.1.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack liblc3-1.1.1-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./liblc3-1.1.1-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/liblc3-1.1.1-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/liblc3-1.1.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/liblc3_1-1.1.1-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/liblc3-devel-1.1.1-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(liblc3)
  /usr/bin/dlc3.exe
  /usr/bin/elc3.exe
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/liblc3.README
  /usr/share/doc/liblc3/CONTRIBUTING.md
  /usr/share/doc/liblc3/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/liblc3/README.md

(liblc3_1)
  /usr/bin/cyglc3-1.dll

(liblc3-devel)
  /usr/include/lc3.h
  /usr/include/lc3_cpp.h
  /usr/include/lc3_private.h
  /usr/lib/liblc3.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/lc3.pc

